'''Kevin O'Sullivan''' (born c. 1960) is the editor of ''[[The Irish Times]]'' newspaper. He succeeded [[Geraldine Kennedy]] on 23 June 2011 upon her retirement.<ref>[http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2011/0623/breaking55.html O'Sullivan appointed 'Irish Times' Editor] ''Irish Times'', 23 June 2011.</ref>

O'Sullivan is from [[Tramore]], [[County Waterford]]. He earned a [[Bachelor of Science]] degree from [[University College Dublin]] in 1981 and a diploma in [[Journalism]] from [[Dublin City University]] in 1983. He worked at the ''[[Connacht Tribune]]'' and the ''[[Tuam Herald]]'' before joining the ''Irish Times'' in 1997.

He was news editor at the ''Times'' from 2006<U+2013>2011. He previously held the positions of night editor, special projects editor, editor of the Health supplement and environmental and food science correspondent.

He has a wife, Ger, and two sons and a daughter.

